Eat Natural, the Essex-based fruit and nut bar maker that exports to more than 20 countries, discovered that the man it had appointed as its exclusive distributor in Italy really sold to only a few retailers in Milan. Fortunately it quickly realised its mistake and exports now account for 35pc of the firm's total sales. Co-founder Parveen Vijh said: "We work really, really hard to create strong, productive relationships with our sales teams abroad. Every market is different, and you really need to tune into that."
